HEADWORD: Lockout
<hw>Lock"out`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The closing of a
factory or workshop by an employer, usually in order to bring the
workmen to satisfactory terms by a suspension of wages.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

